Deputy President William Ruto has continued to suffer blow after blow in Kisii county following the defection of his key allies. On Monday, UDA party treasurer and Kisii County governor aspirant  Omingo Magara ditched his party for the Jubilee party. Before him, Kisii County deputy governor  Joash Maangi and former youth secretary at the DP's office Anthony Kibagendi had announced their defection. South Mugurango MP Sylvanus Osoro has however remained loyal to the DP.